OL,6,FThe first ever Eurovision was made
OL,7,Fmemorable by the winning act
OL,8,Fforgetting her lines.
OL,10,FOnly seven nations competed in the
OL,11,F1956 contest held in Lugano,
OL,12,FSwitzerland.
OL,14,FThe host country singer, Lys Assia,
OL,15,Fwas crowned the winner, with the song
OL,16,F'Refrain'. But during a repeat
OL,17,Fperformance, Assia forgot the words.
OL,19,FTune into the ITV News entertainment
OL,20,Fpodcast, Unscripted...
