OL,6,FPortugal's entry starts a revolution
OL,8,FFifty years ago, Portugal entered the
OL,9,Fcontest with a song that became
OL,10,Fsynonymous with revolution in the
OL,11,Fcountry.
OL,13,FPaulo de Carvalho's song, 'E Depois Do
OL,14,FAdeus', was used by radio stations in
OL,15,F1974 as a signal to ready the
OL,16,FCarnation revolution forces to take on
OL,17,Fthe authoritarian government.
OL,19,FBut the song made less of an impact on
OL,20,Fthe Eurovision judges - it came in
OL,21,Flast place, with just three points.
